The agent formatted the timeRange parameter values with a "Z" (Zulu/UTC indicator) and set the end time to "2024-02-15T23:59:59Z" instead of matching the expected "2024-02-15T00:00:00" format, causing a mismatch with the required function call signature.

The agent made two separate function calls for related actions that should have been combined into a single call, passing both sslTlsManagement and dataAtRestEncryption parameters together as required by the tool's expected input structure.

The agent omitted the "historical": false field in the traffic_data argument and used the incomplete location "123 Market St" instead of "123 Market St, San Francisco", causing the function call parameters to not match the expected format.

The root cause is a mismatch in parameter naming: the agent used "arguments" instead of the required "parameters" for the function call, resulting in the evaluator not recognizing the invocation despite otherwise correct tool and argument selection.

The agent only included one digital display instead of the required two, and the display content did not match exactly ("our latest product video" vs. "latest product video"), leading to a mismatch with the expected function call parameters.

The model output the function call in a <tool_call> tag with JSON, rather than using the required structured function call format expected by the environment, leading to a mismatch and evaluator error despite correct parameters.

The agent formatted the "timeWindow" field's "start" and "end" values using the ISO 8601 format with a "Z" suffix for UTC ("2020-03-01T00:00:00Z"), while the expected format omits the "Z" and has seconds as "00" (no "Z" and no seconds for "end"). This mismatch caused the evaluator to reject the function call.
